## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="4354b-156">在大多数情况下返回的值<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit.Text%2A>和<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit.LexicalForm%2A>完全相同。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4354b-156">In most cases the values returned by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit.Text%2A> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit.LexicalForm%2A> are identical.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4354b-157">但是，识别引擎可以使用语音规范化返回更加用户友好或口语文本表示形式的音频输入。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4354b-157">However, recognition engines may use speech normalization to return more user-friendly or colloquial text representations of audio input.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="4354b-158">语音规范化是使用的特殊构造或符号表示中编写的语音。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4354b-158">Speech normalization is the use of special constructs or symbols to express speech in writing.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4354b-159">例如，规范化可以说出的单词"美元和十六个美分"将替换为"$1.16"中输出文本。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4354b-159">For example, normalization can replace the spoken words "a dollar and sixteen cents" with "$1.16" in output text.</span></span>  
  
   
  
